In this article, President Biden addresses the congregation at St. Mark's Episcopal Church in Washington, D.C. He acknowledges the pain and loss experienced by the families affected by gun violence, including his own personal experience of losing family members. He praises the courage of the attendees and their ability to turn their pain into purpose. The President highlights the need for stricter gun laws and urges for common-sense measures to be taken, such as limiting the number of bullets and banning assault weapons. He references previous successful efforts in the '90s and expresses confidence in being able to make progress again. He concludes by emphasizing the importance of remembering the victims and asks for a moment of silence to honor them.